1. You need to give your radio buttons a name. Radio buttons are grouped by all having the same name. E.g.
```
&lt;input name=&quot;choice&quot; type=&quot;radio&quot; value=&quot;paper&quot;&gt;Paper
```

2. You&#39;re missing the Rock button.

3. There&#39;s no need to assign anything to the `onclick` property of the radio buttons. Just set a variable to the random selection from the array to get the computer&#39;s choice:

```
computer_choice = types[ Math.floor(Math.random()*(types.length))];
```

You can get the value of the user&#39;s selection with:

```
var user_button = document.querySelector(&quot;input[name=choice]:checked&quot;);
if (user_button) {
    var user_choice = user_button.value;
} else {
    alert(&quot;You have to choose Rock, Paper, or Scissoer first&quot;);
}
```
