            fileList.push(blob);
        }
       //console.log(fileList);
       console.log(fileList.length);
    };
    

And the reason why? 

Placing the `console.log` outside of the AJAX will not work as the AJAX will work on a different thread in the background but the `console.log` call will be run on main thread. See [*How do I return the response from an asynchronous call?*](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/14220321/how-do-i-return-the-response-from-an-asynchronous-call) for a lot more detail.

The other thing you are doing is overwriting your `0` index element of `fileList` with the `fileList[0] = blob;`. You will need to change that to `fileList.push(blob);` to add the object to the array.

